&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East Suffolk and North Essex NHS Foundation Trust has a variety of exciting nursing opportunities both full and part time across all of our sites: Colchester Hospital, Ipswich Hospital and Community sites of East Suffolk. We welcome applications from final year adult student nurses, newly qualified registered adult nurses and Band 5 experienced registered nurses.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For student nurses we offer many opportunities for learning and support, which continues throughout your transition from student to Registered Nurse.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ESNEFT’s offer to you:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;High quality 12 months Preceptorship Programme followed by ongoing continuing development opportunities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A named Preceptor from day 1&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Internal Transfer Scheme allowing you to transfer between different areas across ESNEFT, including a large range of specialties across all sites&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;***It is important that you identify two preferred areas of clinical interest (the nursing speciality rather than the Ward name, as these are subject to change) and preferred site of work. Please provide this information within your supporting statement on your application form to help us plan for your interview.*** &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;‘&lt;em&gt;Please note that this role is subject to a DBS check which will be charged to the successful candidate. Full details can be found within the ‘DBS Information’ documents attached to this advert.’&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead Practice Education Facilitator - Liz Numadi&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; liz.numadi@esneft.nhs.uk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
